In [112]:
sns.boxplot(x="speeding", y="total", data=df)
plt.xlabel("Speeding")
plt.ylabel("Total Accidents")
plt.xticks(rotation=90)
plt.tick_params(axis='x', labelsize=7)
plt.show()

Inference: The above box plot shows that accidents involving speeding tend to have a higher median total accident count compared to non-speeding accidents.

In [120]:
x = df['speeding']
y = df['alcohol']
z = df['total']
fig = plt.figure(figsize=(15, 15))
ax = fig.add_subplot(111, projection='3d')
ax.scatter(x, y, z, c='blue', marker='o', s=30)
ax.set_title("3D Scatter Plot of Car Crashes")
ax.set_xlabel("Speeding")
ax.set_ylabel("Alcohol")
ax.set_zlabel("Total Accidents")
plt.show()

A 3D Scatter plot between speeding,alcohol and total accidents.
